  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support to the most vulnerable communities in their own efforts to meet urgent humanitarian needs.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;Beneficiary identification and registration
&#x2022;Beneficiary verification  
&#x2022;Training on good fishing and fish preservation techniques to make fish available to the communities all year round
&#x2022;Trainings on improved techniques and community ownership
&#x2022;Distribution of seeds and fishing gears
&#x2022;Distribution of village saving and loans association kits
&#x2022;Training on improved farming techniques which include seed and grain preservation skills so as to allow farmers use it over the following years. 
&#x2022;Training to the village saving and loans associations to implement small trade and savings to diversify their family income and provide the cash during crisis. 
&#x2022;Refresher training to water user committee members and pump mechanics skills to strengthen and ensure the local community has the capacity to continue ensuring that safe water is accessible and capacity exists to keep them in good running conditions.</narrative>
  </description>
